<subSubSection id="C3266566FFD484766EC6FDBE0E479B22" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8336EDFFD484766EC6FDBE0E479B22" blockId="4.[151,1437,513,1079]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="B948EAFFFFD484766EC6FDBE0E2B9D92" bold="true" box="[151,269,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to Article 45.5 of the Code (ICZN 1999), “A name expressly proposed to denote an infrasubspecific entity … is not an available name …”. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B1CFFD484766C99FD420C4E9DBE" author="Arnold, G." box="[712,872,657,683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" pagination="284 - 396" refId="ref8490" refString="Arnold, G. (1932) The Psammocharidae (olim Pompilidae) of the Ethiopian region. Part I. Subfamily Pepsinae. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 14, 284 - 396." type="journal article" year="1932">Arnold (1932)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D6EFFD484766D8AFD420B009DBE" authorityName="Wahis" authorityYear="2000" box="[987,1062,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Hemipepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiogae">
<emphasis id="B948EAFFFFD484766D8AFD420B009DBE" box="[987,1062,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">kiogae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a variety of a “race” (=subspecies) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D6EFFD484766EA2FD650D5C9DDA" authority="(Klug, 1834)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[243,634,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Hemipepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabrata">
<emphasis id="B948EAFFFFD484766EA2FD650EFB9DDA" box="[243,477,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Hemipepsis glabrata</emphasis>
(Klug, 1834)
</taxonomicName>
. It is thus clear that 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D6EFFD484766D31FD660C8D9DDA" authorityName="Wahis" authorityYear="2000" box="[864,939,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Hemipepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiogae">
<emphasis id="B948EAFFFFD484766D31FD660C8D9DDA" box="[864,939,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">kiogae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not available from Arnold’s paper. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B1CFFD484766B06FD660FC89DE6" author="Wahis, R." pageId="4" pageNumber="157" pagination="73 - 100" refId="ref12937" refString="Wahis, R. (2000 a) Hymenopteres aculeates du Yemen (Pompilidae, Vespidae). Notes Fauniques de Gembloux, 41, 73 - 100." type="journal article" year="2000">Wahis (2000a)</bibRefCitation>
proposed a new status (“stat. n.”) for 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D6EFFD484766CFCFD0A0DDE9DE6" authorityName="Wahis" authorityYear="2000" box="[685,760,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Hemipepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiogae">
<emphasis id="B948EAFFFFD484766CFCFD0A0DDE9DE6" box="[685,760,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">kiogae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as a valid species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D6EFFD484766DACFD090BA69DE6" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1843" box="[1021,1152,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Hemipepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B948EAFFFFD484766DACFD090BA69DE6" box="[1021,1152,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Hemipepsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although attributing the name to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B1CFFD484766EA7FD2E0EBC9C02" author="Arnold, G." box="[246,410,765,791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" pagination="284 - 396" refId="ref8490" refString="Arnold, G. (1932) The Psammocharidae (olim Pompilidae) of the Ethiopian region. Part I. Subfamily Pepsinae. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 14, 284 - 396." type="journal article" year="1932">Arnold (1932)</bibRefCitation>
. Article 45.5.1 of the Code deals directly with situations such as this, specifying that such a name is thereby established as new with its own authorship and date (Wahis, 
<quantity id="4CC49B08FFD484766DAAFCF20B769C2E" box="[1019,1104,801,827]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" unit="in" value="2000.0">2000 in</quantity>
this case). Effectively, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B1CFFD484766B06FCF20FC89C4A" author="Wahis, R." pageId="4" pageNumber="157" pagination="73 - 100" refId="ref12937" refString="Wahis, R. (2000 a) Hymenopteres aculeates du Yemen (Pompilidae, Vespidae). Notes Fauniques de Gembloux, 41, 73 - 100." type="journal article" year="2000">Wahis (2000a)</bibRefCitation>
proposed a new name for an entity which had previously been described from two female specimens collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F32B767DFFD484766EAEFCBA0E709C96" box="[255,342,873,899]" name="Uganda" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Uganda</collectingCountry>
(the “ 
<typeStatus id="5487884FFFD484766FCDFCBA0EF79C96" box="[412,465,873,899]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">type</typeStatus>
” deposited in the Natural History Museum, London) but for which there was no valid name. Even though Wahis did not specify that the name was new, Article 16.1 (which requires such a designation for names proposed after 1999) is actually fulfilled by conforming with the recommended treatment of former names of infrasubspecific entities which are indicated as “stat. nov.” in Recommendation 16A. Furthermore, since this is effectively a new replacement name, the requirements of Article 16.4 are met, the 
<typeStatus id="5487884FFFD484766A78FC2A0B7F9B06" box="[1065,1113,1017,1043]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">type</typeStatus>
material being that specified by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B1CFFD484766EE8FBCE0E7B9B22" author="Arnold, G." box="[185,349,1053,1079]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" pagination="284 - 396" refId="ref8490" refString="Arnold, G. (1932) The Psammocharidae (olim Pompilidae) of the Ethiopian region. Part I. Subfamily Pepsinae. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 14, 284 - 396." type="journal article" year="1932">Arnold (1932)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
